 :itonami.blueprint/domain :bearings-gears/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :materials-safety :equipment-safety]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :bearings-gears-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "BearGearAdvisor ⊣ Bearings, Gears and Driving Elements Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for bearing/gear/driving-element
 manufacturing (precision-machining/heat-treatment/grinding lines
 producing finished ball bearings, roller bearings, spur gears, helical
 gears and worm gears) -- not direct machining/grinding-line-equipment
 control authority and not tolerance-class-certification authority
 (e.g. ISO 492 bearing tolerance class or AGMA/ISO 1328 gear quality
 mark). Four ops (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct machining/
 grinding-line-equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate block,
 permanent tolerance-class-certification-authority block (this actor
 never self-issues a bearing/gear tolerance-class conformance mark),
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged production quantity, double-schedule
 guard, product-type validation, dimensional-tolerance plausibility
 validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern
 flagging (materials-safety/equipment-safety concern) ALWAYS escalates
 to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
